   288вҶ’/// The `Error` type, a wrapper around a dynamic error type.
   289вҶ’///
   290вҶ’/// `Error` works a lot like `Box<dyn std::error::Error>`, but with these
   291вҶ’/// differences:
   292вҶ’///
   293вҶ’/// - `Error` requires that the error is `Send`, `Sync`, and `'static`.
   294вҶ’/// - `Error` guarantees that a backtrace is available, even if the underlying
   295вҶ’///   error type does not provide one.
   296вҶ’/// - `Error` is represented as a narrow pointer &mdash; exactly one word in
   297вҶ’///   size instead of two.
   298вҶ’///
   299вҶ’/// <br>
   300вҶ’///
   301вҶ’/// # Display representations
